            <thetext>Split the public and protected API:

* protected:

_setStyleProperty(elementId, key, value);
_getStyleProperty(elementId, key);

elementId could be something like &quot;_element&quot;, &quot;_inputElement&quot;, ...

This would allow to apply styles and properties also to inner elements. There would also be a new method _createElement(elementId, tagName), which automatically creates the element, store it, and sync the current values to the element.

* public

setStyleProperty(key, value);
getStyleProperty(key, value);

Mark both methods in this case with big warning signs that they may break the system if used in a wrong way.</thetext>
